This paper discusses a data mining approach, specifically granular association rule mining, which is commonly studied in the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of discretization approaches on mining stronger rules, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses a real-life dataset and discusses the generation of rules, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
